(674, 3, '2018-10-22 10:27:07', '2018-10-22 10:27:07', '<em>For a Bangladeshi wedding to be successful, we, the guests, can forgive anything except the quality of the food you serve us. However, if you’re the kind of person that wishes to infuse a different type of cuisine or dish to the dining, but you are unsure whether your guests would like it or not, w</em><em>e are here to provide you with a variety of striking, non-clichéd, and nontraditional wedding dishes that we have found online and that you can make use of- especially for events taking place indoors. Here are some of our favorites:</em>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h4><strong>Tarka Aloo and Luchi.</strong></h4>\r\n<strong> <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-670 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/kRQt5TUcS2Sb46wPCryi_aloo-gobi-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>Potatoes: 1/2 kg</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Yellow Food Color: 1 pinch</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Corn flour: 2 tablespoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>National Vinegar : 3 tablespoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Water: 1 liter</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Green Chilies: 4, finely chopped</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Fresh Coriander Few leaves</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil: 1/2 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Masala: 1 packet (50 grams)</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Kneaded Dough: half kg</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>For Filling:</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Daal Chana: 250 grams, boiled</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Cumin Seed: 1 teaspoon, toasted</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Green Chilies: 4, chopped</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Garlic: 1 tablespoon, chopped</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil: For frying</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>-</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Scrub the potatoes well and cut into thick round slices.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Leave the skin on. Bring a liter of water to the boil and cook the potatoes for half an hour.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When tender, mash them with a wooden spoon.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Dissolve the cornflour in half a cup of water and stir into the mashed potatoes.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Turn off the heat when the mixture thickens.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Fold in the yellow food color, vinegar, green chilies and coriander leaves.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Heat the oil in a separate pan, turn off the heat and add the Masala.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Let the masala fry for a while, then pour the oil over the potatoes and mix well.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>-</em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Grind the boiled daal chana and mix in Masala, Chat Masala, garlic, green chilies, salt, and cumin seed.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Set aside for the flavors to meld. Meanwhile, divide the dough into small balls.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Flatten the balls slightly and stuff with 1 tbsp of daal mixture.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Fold the dough over the mixture to encase it inside.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Lightly roll out each ball into a small pancake.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Heat the oil in a wok, drop in a pair of luchi’s at a time and deep fry until golden and crisp.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Serve hot with Pickle.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis is a dish that will be best suited as an appetizer for indoor programs during the evening. If you’re planning a Haldi or Mehendi event on your rooftop or on your home garden, you can set up a counter on your porch or rooftop and serve on a refill basis.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Gola Kabab</strong></h4>\r\n<strong> <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-667 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image003-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>A soft kabab that melts in your mouth. It is a barbecue favorite which is so simple, yet appetizing.</em></p>\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>Beef : 1 kg, cubed</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Fried Onions : 250 grams</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Ginger Garlic Paste : 1 tablespoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Yogurt : 4 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Coconut Powder : 4 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Raw Papaya : 2 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Green Chilies : 4</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil : As required</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Strong Thread or String : As required</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Masala : 1 packet (50 grams)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Mix the beef with fried onions, ginger garlic paste, coconut powder, green chilies, raw papaya, and Korma Masala.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Grind everything finely, fold in the yogurt, and knead into a well-blended mix.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Leave the mince to rest for an hour.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Press handfuls of the mince onto skewers, wrap securely with string and barbecue over hot coals.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Frequently brush or sprinkle with oil, turn skewers carefully to ensure kababs remain intact.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When cooked through, serve with fresh salad and raita.</em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>\r\n\r\nLike the tarka aloo, this dish is also an indoor meal of sorts. However, as this is a heavy meal, this suits best as a side to the main course alongside Polao, biriyani or Kacchi.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong> Afghani Pulao</strong></h4>\r\n<em><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-668 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image005-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" />This recipe is a delectable marriage between the self-effacing khichuri and the extravagant pulao with the amalgamation of daal.</em>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-672\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Veg_Handi_1600-737x1024.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"889\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>Rice : 3 cups</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil : 1 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Onion (sliced) : 2 medium</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Mutton : 750 gm</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>National Ginger &amp; Garlic Paste : 1 tablespoon each</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Pulao Masala : 1/2 packet</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Carrots (grated) : 1 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Raisins : 2 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Sugar : 2 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Almonds (blanched) : 10</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Pistachios (blanched) : 10</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Wash and soak rice for at least 3 hours and keep changing the water every hour.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>In a large pot, fry the onions till dark brown in color. Strain, crush and keep aside.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>In the same oil add the mutton, National Ginger Paste, and National Garlic Paste. Cook until the meat is slightly brown.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Now add Pulao Masala and 6-7 cups of water; bring to a full boil then turn the heat low and simmer till the meat is tender. If required add Iodized Salt to taste.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>In a small saucepan add carrots, raisins, sugar and 1/2 cup water. Cook on medium heat until the carrots get softened and liquid dries out. Keep aside.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Add crushed fried onions to the mutton gravy that depart a deep caramel flavor and color to the gravy.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When the meat is ready, strain the soaked rice and add to the meat. Cook over a high heat until most of the liquid disappears. You should have enough liquid left to cook rice in. You may add some additional hot water if required.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Turn the heat low.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Serve the pulao with the carrots, and raisins. Generously garnish with blanched almonds and pistachios.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis delicious and extravagant dish is an all-event-purpose dish, however, Afghani pulao tastes best when cooked slow and served hot. We recommend you to make this dish during Aakhd or Mehedi nights with a fewer number of guests as catering this pulao is a complex process and it will require a lot of labor and time to serve a greater number of guests.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Fried Chops Recipe</strong></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-669 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image007-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />Typical chops made special with a unique frying method which will give you a scrumptious meal.</em></p>\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>chops : 1 kg</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Onions : 2</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Ginger Garlic Paste : 2 teaspoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Vinegar : half cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Eggs : 2</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Breadcrumbs : 1 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil For frying</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Masala : 1 packet (50 grams)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>In a deep pot, combine the onions, chops, ginger garlic paste, Masala, vinegar and 2 glasses of water.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Set on medium heat to cook.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When the chops are tender, remove them from the pot and let cool.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Dip the cooled chops first in beaten egg, then in breadcrumbs and deep fry to a crispy golden color.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFried Chops are comparatively easy to cook and serve, but it is absolutely necessary that they are freshly fried. Having them fried 2-3 hours before serving will deteriorate its taste and make it look unappealing. Traditionally fried chops are an essential fine-dine menu in Pakistan during the wedding, but we recommend this dish for Aakhd during the winter season.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Source: <a href=\"http://www.madeeasy.com.pk\">www.madeeasy.com.pk</a></em>', 'An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '578-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-10-22 10:27:07', '2018-10-22 10:27:07', '', 578, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/22/578-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(884, 4, '2019-01-02 12:13:03', '2019-01-02 12:13:03', '<em>In Old Dhaka, kebabs, naans, bakharkhani, kachchi and, haleem, bhuna khichuri, and tehari are found in almost every corner of the street. It is from these areas of Old Dhaka that the tradition of biriyani has spread out among all restaurants in Dhaka city. However, the kachchi biryani is possibly the most lovely and genuine dhakaiya biryani that I have ever tasted. It is so widely appreciated that Kachchi Biriyani has now become an included dish at weddings, parties, and festivities in Bangladesh.</em>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-812\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image005-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" />\n<h3>DELICIOUS LAYERS OF MEAT &amp; RICE</h3>\nThe term ‘kachchi’ means raw. Referring to the ingredients being cooked raw, in layers, instead of separately adding cooked meat and rice. Layers of meat, rice, and potatoes are infused with delicious blends of fragrant spices to make the kachchi biryani.\n\nRegardless of whether it is the delicate piece of the mutton, the tater, or the rice itself, every dollop is a heavenly delight.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-813\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image008.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"522\" height=\"327\" />\n\nKachchi Biriyani takes lesser time to cook too than other traditional biriyani’s. All the ingredients are mixed in layers and then cooked in the oven instead of separately cooking the rice, meat and then mixing all of them.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-811\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"374\" />\n<h3>DO IT YOURSELF!</h3>\nNewbie Chefs, like myself, can prepare this grand biriyani at home with ease. After mixing all the ingredients, cook the biriyani in the microwave oven for 1.5-2 hrs. Taking it out sooner might leave the meat undercooked. Traditionally, the sealing process of the cooking pot is done with dough. However, using a lid that perfectly fits the cooking pan also gets the job done. Especially if you’re a novice cook, this technique saves you time and causes no muggy fingers.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-820\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Beef-Biryani.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" />\n<h3>APPETIZERS AND DESSERTS</h3>\n&nbsp;\n\nA simple salad of carrots, cucumbers, onions etc- is just enough as a side for kachchi biryani. As an appetizer, you can serve Borhani. For desserts, you can never go wrong with, Mishti bhaat or Morabba- made from chal kumra.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-821\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/pulav_1447762978.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"660\" height=\"370\" /> <img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-822\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/lassi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"537\" /> <img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-823\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/20171220-salted-mint-lassi-borhani-vicky-wasik-11-1500x1125-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" />\n\nWith time, you will learn to master the art of cooking Kacchi adding a variety of spices and experimenting. Your hard work will be paid off when you gather your family and friends around the dining table. Hear them enjoy and laugh together while savoring each and every bite of the mouthwatering Biryani.\n\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\n<h3>KACHCHI SPOTS</h3>\nIf cooking isn’t your cup of tea, you can still have a mouthful of this delicacy in some popular restaurants. Namely- Al Rajjak, Star Kabab Banani, Fakhruddin, Handi, Sultan Dine’s etc.<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-815\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image010-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>**Pictures taken from the internet</em>', 'THE KACHCHI CULTURE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '572-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-01-02 12:13:03', '2019-01-02 12:13:03', '', 572, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2019/01/02/572-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
