(299, 3, '2018-07-16 11:02:51', '2018-07-16 11:02:51', 'If this is your first time visiting Bangladesh since many years, or this is your first time ever here and coincidentally you\'ve been invited to your first deshi wedding during your stay, you may be inquisitive about what’s going to go down. Here we will look at some basic situations “newbies” face at our highly inimitable-traditional wedding.', 'WHAT TO EXPECT AT BENGALI WEDDING EVENTS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '276-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-16 11:02:51', '2018-07-16 11:02:51', '', 276, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/07/16/276-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(300, 3, '2018-07-16 11:26:03', '2018-07-16 11:26:03', 'If this is your first time visiting Bangladesh since many years, or this is your first time ever here and coincidentally you\'ve been invited to your first deshi wedding during your stay, you may be inquisitive about what’s going to go down. Here we will look at some basic situations “newbies” face at our highly inimitable-traditional wedding.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-277\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1277\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\n<strong>What to wear</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-279\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image005.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\nThe brighter the better. If you’re a woman, don\'t be petrified to take up a bold color attire. This will help you blend in with the guests who\'ll be dressed in vivacious colors and stunning jewelry- A saree or Lehenga is the trend. For men, you can never go wrong with a suit or a dark color Punjabi with a coati.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-280\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image007.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1686\" height=\"1071\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Length of Wedding</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA traditional bengali wedding celebrations last an average of 7 days.  Usually, the celebration begins after the more official “Aakhd” ceremony. With Haldi nights arranged by both the brides and grooms, followed by the wedding day and then the reception.\r\n\r\nHowever, couples nowadays take the ceremony a step further by arranging bridal showers, Sangeet etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>What can you expect to see at the wedding day?</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-285\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image017.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"955\" />\r\n\r\nOne of the first things that might surprise Western/Non-Bangladeshi-resident guests is the bride’s and groom’s procession. For this, the groom and bride arrives to the ceremony on a flower decorated car. The bride is usually the first one to make the entrance. Guests dance around them to the beat of a dhol, a traditional drum. After that, the bride and groom meet along with their family.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-292\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image031.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"953\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\n<strong>What will the Haldi/Holud ceremony be like?</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-289\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image025.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1428\" height=\"952\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\nIt\'s a fun party! The relatives of both the bride and groom take to the stages for a dance face off with the in laws’ family with choreographed dances. This makes the occasion more fun as it brings the families and cousins together and give the little ones something to look forward to. Because Hey! Who doesn’t like to dance silly in front of hundreds of guest along with your friends and cousins. The day ends with either some sweet EDM played by a DJ or some pop songs played by a local band.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-291\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image029.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\n<strong>FOOD!</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-293\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image033.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1054\" height=\"701\" />\r\n\r\nFor me, arguably the most important part of the wedding. Food is served in batches and the menu usually consists of Borhani, Polao, chicken/beef curry, vegetables, roasted chicken and if you’re lucky you might be served Kacchi. The heavy meal is then finished off by desserts like firni, jorda or mishtibhaat (Sweet rice).\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-294\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image035.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"393\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Should you bring a gift?</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-295\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image037.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"952\" />\r\n\r\nYou are not bound to. But if you do want to gift them something, avoid buying crockeries as they will get hundreds of similar crockeries on the day. Anything else will be a blessing!', 'WHAT TO EXPECT AT BENGALI WEDDING EVENTS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '276-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-16 11:26:03', '2018-07-16 11:26:03', '', 276, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/07/16/276-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(301, 3, '2018-07-16 11:29:21', '2018-07-16 11:29:21', 'If this is your first time visiting Bangladesh since many years, or this is your first time ever here and coincidentally you\'ve been invited to your first deshi wedding during your stay, you may be inquisitive about what’s going to go down. Here we will look at some basic situations “newbies” face at our highly inimitable-traditional wedding.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-277\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1277\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n<h3><strong>What to wear</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-279\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image005.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n\r\nThe brighter the better. If you’re a woman, don\'t be petrified to take up a bold color attire. This will help you blend in with the guests who\'ll be dressed in vivacious colors and stunning jewelry- A saree or Lehenga is the trend. For men, you can never go wrong with a suit or a dark color Punjabi with a coati.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-280\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image007.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1686\" height=\"1071\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Length of Wedding</strong></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA traditional bengali wedding celebrations last an average of 7 days.  Usually, the celebration begins after the more official “Aakhd” ceremony. With Haldi nights arranged by both the brides and grooms, followed by the wedding day and then the reception.\r\n\r\nHowever, couples nowadays take the ceremony a step further by arranging bridal showers, Sangeet etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>What can you expect to see at the wedding day?</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-285\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image017.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"955\" />\r\n\r\nOne of the first things that might surprise Western/Non-Bangladeshi-resident guests is the bride’s and groom’s procession. For this, the groom and bride arrives to the ceremony on a flower decorated car. The bride is usually the first one to make the entrance. Guests dance around them to the beat of a dhol, a traditional drum. After that, the bride and groom meet along with their family.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-292\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image031.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"953\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n<h3><strong>What will the Haldi/Holud ceremony be like?</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-289\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image025.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1428\" height=\"952\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n<h4>It\'s a fun party! The relatives of both the bride and groom take to the stages for a dance face off with the in laws’ family with choreographed dances. This makes the occasion more fun as it brings the families and cousins together and give the little ones something to look forward to. Because Hey! Who doesn’t like to dance silly in front of hundreds of guest along with your friends and cousins. The day ends with either some sweet EDM played by a DJ or some pop songs played by a local band.</h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-291\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image029.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n\r\nPhoto Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography\r\n<h3><strong>FOOD!</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-293\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image033.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1054\" height=\"701\" />\r\n\r\nFor me, arguably the most important part of the wedding. Food is served in batches and the menu usually consists of Borhani, Polao, chicken/beef curry, vegetables, roasted chicken and if you’re lucky you might be served Kacchi. The heavy meal is then finished off by desserts like firni, jorda or mishtibhaat (Sweet rice).\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-294\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image035.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"590\" height=\"393\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Should you bring a gift?</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-295\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image037.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"952\" />\r\n<h4>You are not bound to. But if you do want to gift them something, avoid buying crockeries as they will get hundreds of similar crockeries on the day. Anything else will be a blessing!</h4>', 'WHAT TO EXPECT AT BENGALI WEDDING EVENTS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '276-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-16 11:29:21', '2018-07-16 11:29:21', '', 276, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/07/16/276-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
