(481, 1, '2018-10-10 07:29:09', '2018-10-10 07:29:09', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The idea behind dressing up for a Bangladeshi wedding ceremony is to dress to look the part of the wedding guest. Since the idea is to blend in with the mass while also making yourself stand out via your sense of style, a simple but elegant dress with non-over-pouring jewelry will make you stand apart among a crowd that is garbed in vibrant celebratory colors.</p>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-3.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"543\" height=\"362\" />\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: MAT Photography</h6>\r\n[INSERT_ELEMENTOR id=\"443\"]\r\n<h3><strong>Don’t Skip Jewelry</strong></h3>\r\nA saree or a lehenga looks half-finished if not ornamented with the right jewelry. Pick a pair of Dangles or Stud earrings for your ears. And don’t forget to adorn your neck. A meek gold chain with a glistening pendant will be enough to complete your outfit.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-356 \" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-10-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"406\" height=\"608\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:জলছাপ</p>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-347 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-1.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"421\" height=\"632\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Mate</p>\r\n\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Haldi Ceremony</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"wp-image-350 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-4.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"531\" height=\"354\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-346 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/vgsgfvg.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"529\" height=\"352\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\nSince the event consists of you applying turmeric paste on the bride and groom, try to avoid long or over hanging dresses. The more you wear, the harder it will be for you to handle the excessive clothing materials in the midst of the crowd, and more the chances of you staining your precious clothes. A simple kamiz or kurta is enough.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-351 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-5.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"522\" height=\"348\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Photoholic</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Wedding Ceremony &amp; Reception</strong></h3>\r\n<strong> </strong>The wedding and reception ceremony is a great time for you to try out various designer wears and the latest trends, however, we presage you to not go over the top in excitement.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, rule out blatantly simple attires like salwars or kurtas. Since the wedding is a traditional event, it is best for you to be garbed in traditional clothing. Gowns, trousers, crop-top, skirts or anything too close-fitting or skimpy is a huge NO.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-352 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-6.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"423\" height=\"635\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\nYour best option is to go with a Saree or the second best attire- Lehenga. If you’re a guest at the wedding, don’t wear anything too bright or a saree or lehenga that is covered with embroideries or embellishments. Wedding Reception', 'What to wear to a Bangladeshi wedding as a female guest', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '343-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 07:29:09', '2018-10-10 07:29:09', '', 343, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/10/343-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(599, 4, '2018-10-17 05:54:58', '2018-10-17 05:54:58', 'We know if given the opportunity, you would take every chance to make your wedding events stand out from the rest. Who does not want their wedding to be unique and different and attract all the attention? Therefore, we have come up with 4 OUT-OF-THE-BOX themes that you can apply to your own wedding!\r\n<h3><strong>Indoor Garden</strong></h3>\r\nThe theme is best suited for the summer season. The look will definitely brighten up and give a more natural atmosphere with a smell of freshness to indoor venues with zero natural beauty. Covering the walls in green leaves, small plants spread throughout the corners with suspending lanterns, while fencing the dinner area with green hanging chandeliers. Turn your experience of a closed banquet hall into a sensation of being outdoors.\r\n<h3><strong>Vintage</strong></h3>\r\nVintage will never go out of style. This theme will set a classy and elegant mood throughout the event. Wishy-washy colors, lots of antique showpieces, mirrors, white pearls used instead of flowers to decorate table tops, and lots of white candles. For extra mood setting, use English teacups as centerpieces for tables.\r\nFor extra mood setting, you can take all your pictures in black and white or in a specific retro filter.\r\n<h3><strong>Glamor</strong></h3>\r\nThe theme should be black and gold/white themed event. However, for absolute aesthetics, the guests need to be dressed in black and gold/white too. Although this seems like a tremendous task to ask your guests to dress to complement the theme, we can’t help but admire how beautiful it looks. It is necessary to address the fact that this is best suited for Engagement or Anniversary events. Again, Lots of candles are required and red roses are thrown around to give a contrast. Use Black and Gold helium balloons to cover corners of the ceilings. Curtain an entire wall with strings attached with bulbs.\r\n<h3><strong>Paper Origami</strong></h3>\r\nThis theme is Ideal for the Mehendi nights or Sangeet Nights. Using paper might sound very simplistic, However, it is very economical but still gives a beautiful artistry to your event. Swapping real flowers for paper flowers on the tables, hanging bright origami cranes from the ceiling instead of flowers or chandeliers, and using large floral ribbons to curtain a wall-making the picture-perfect background for your photo booth. Use paper flowers in steel pots as centerpieces. What’s beautiful about this theme is, you can engage your relatives and little cousins in making and decorating origamis so that everyone feels included.', '4 OUT-OF-THE-BOX Themes for Wedding events', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '523-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-17 05:54:58', '2018-10-17 05:54:58', '', 523, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/17/523-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
