(888, 4, '2019-01-02 12:20:57', '2019-01-02 12:20:57', '<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">If this is your first time visiting Bangladesh since many years, or this is your first time ever here and coincidentally you\'ve been invited to your first Bangladeshi wedding during your stay, you may be inquisitive about what’s going to go down. Here we will look at some basic situations “newbies” face at our highly inimitable-traditional wedding.</h5>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-277\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1277\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>What to wear</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-279\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image005.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">The brighter the better. If you’re a woman, don\'t be petrified to take up a bold color attire. This will help you blend in with the guests who\'ll be dressed in vivacious colors and stunning jewelry- A saree or Lehenga is the trend. For men, you can never go wrong with a suit or a dark color Punjabi with a coati.</h5>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-311\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/26221012_819266841578274_7157282757849986845_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Length of Wedding</strong></h3>\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">A traditional bengali wedding celebrations last an average of 7 days.  Usually, the celebration begins after the more official “Aakhd” ceremony. With Haldi nights arranged by both the brides and grooms, followed by the wedding day and then the reception.</h5>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-289\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image025.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1428\" height=\"952\" />\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</h5>\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">However, couples nowadays take the ceremony a step further by arranging bridal showers, Sangeet etc.</h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>What can you expect to see at the wedding day?</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-285\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image017.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"955\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Metro Weddings</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">One of the first things that might surprise Western/Non-Bangladeshi-resident guests is the bride’s and groom’s procession. For this, the groom and bride arrives to the ceremony on a flower decorated car. The bride is usually the first one to make the entrance. Guests dance around them to the beat of a dhol, a traditional drum. After that, the bride and groom meet along with their family.</h5>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-292\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image031.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"953\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>What will the Haldi/Holud ceremony be like?</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-313\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/31958060_1797761493623465_1599431853796753408_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">It\'s a fun party! The relatives of both the bride and groom take to the stages for a dance face off with the in laws’ family with choreographed dances. This makes the occasion more fun as it brings the families and cousins together and give the little ones something to look forward to. Because Hey! Who doesn’t like to dance silly in front of hundreds of guest along with your friends and cousins. The day ends with either some sweet EDM played by a DJ or some pop songs played by a local band.</h5>\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-304 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/wm-01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"405\" height=\"606\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Mate</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>FOOD!</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-293\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image033.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1054\" height=\"701\" />\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">For me, arguably the most important part of the wedding. Food is served in batches and the menu usually consists of Borhani, Polao, chicken/beef curry, vegetables, roasted chicken and if you’re lucky you might be served Kacchi. The heavy meal is then finished off by desserts like firni, jorda or mishtibhaat (Sweet rice).</h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-312\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/30821485_1033610443454696_4619924123552844831_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1795\" height=\"1197\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Metro Weddings</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Should you bring a gift?</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-295\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image037.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"952\" />\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">You are not bound to. But if you do want to gift them something, avoid buying crockeries as they will get hundreds of similar crockeries on the day. Anything else will be a blessing!</h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeatured Photo Courtesy: Wedding Diary Bangladesh', 'WHAT TO EXPECT AT BENGALI WEDDING EVENTS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '276-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-02 12:20:57', '2019-01-02 12:20:57', '', 276, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2019/01/02/276-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(889, 4, '2019-01-03 11:24:52', '2019-01-03 11:24:52', '<em>For a Bangladeshi wedding to be successful, we, the guests, can forgive anything except the quality of the food you serve us. However, if you’re the kind of person that wishes to infuse a different type of cuisine or dish to the dining, but you are unsure whether your guests would like it or not, w</em><em>e are here to provide you with a variety of striking, non-clichéd, and nontraditional wedding dishes that we have found online and that you can make use of- especially for events taking place indoors. Here are some of our favorites:</em>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h4><strong>Tarka Aloo and Luchi.</strong></h4>\r\n<strong> <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-670 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/kRQt5TUcS2Sb46wPCryi_aloo-gobi-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>Potatoes: 1/2 kg</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Yellow Food Color: 1 pinch</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Corn flour: 2 tablespoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>National Vinegar : 3 tablespoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Water: 1 liter</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Green Chilies: 4, finely chopped</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Fresh Coriander Few leaves</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil: 1/2 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Masala: 1 packet (50 grams)</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Kneaded Dough: half kg</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>For Filling:</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Daal Chana: 250 grams, boiled</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Cumin Seed: 1 teaspoon, toasted</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Green Chilies: 4, chopped</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Garlic: 1 tablespoon, chopped</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil: For frying</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>-</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Scrub the potatoes well and cut into thick round slices.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Leave the skin on. Bring a liter of water to the boil and cook the potatoes for half an hour.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When tender, mash them with a wooden spoon.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Dissolve the cornflour in half a cup of water and stir into the mashed potatoes.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Turn off the heat when the mixture thickens.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Fold in the yellow food color, vinegar, green chilies and coriander leaves.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Heat the oil in a separate pan, turn off the heat and add the Masala.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Let the masala fry for a while, then pour the oil over the potatoes and mix well.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>-</em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Grind the boiled daal chana and mix in Masala, Chat Masala, garlic, green chilies, salt, and cumin seed.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Set aside for the flavors to meld. Meanwhile, divide the dough into small balls.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Flatten the balls slightly and stuff with 1 tbsp of daal mixture.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Fold the dough over the mixture to encase it inside.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Lightly roll out each ball into a small pancake.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Heat the oil in a wok, drop in a pair of luchi’s at a time and deep fry until golden and crisp.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Serve hot with Pickle.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis is a dish that will be best suited as an appetizer for indoor programs during the evening. If you’re planning a Haldi or Mehendi event on your rooftop or on your home garden, you can set up a counter on your porch or rooftop and serve on a refill basis.\r\n\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n<h4><strong>Gola Kabab</strong></h4>\r\n<strong> <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-667 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image003-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>A soft kabab that melts in your mouth. It is a barbecue favorite which is so simple, yet appetizing.</em></p>\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>Beef : 1 kg, cubed</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Fried Onions : 250 grams</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Ginger Garlic Paste : 1 tablespoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Yogurt : 4 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Coconut Powder : 4 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Raw Papaya : 2 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Green Chilies : 4</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil : As required</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Strong Thread or String : As required</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Masala : 1 packet (50 grams)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Mix the beef with fried onions, ginger garlic paste, coconut powder, green chilies, raw papaya, and Korma Masala.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Grind everything finely, fold in the yogurt, and knead into a well-blended mix.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Leave the mince to rest for an hour.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Press handfuls of the mince onto skewers, wrap securely with string and barbecue over hot coals.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Frequently brush or sprinkle with oil, turn skewers carefully to ensure kababs remain intact.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When cooked through, serve with fresh salad and raita.</em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>\r\n\r\n<em> </em>\r\n\r\nLike the tarka aloo, this dish is also an indoor meal of sorts. However, as this is a heavy meal, this suits best as a side to the main course alongside Polao, biriyani or Kacchi.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong> Afghani Pulao</strong></h4>\r\n<em><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-668 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image005-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" />This recipe is a delectable marriage between the self-effacing khichuri and the extravagant pulao with the amalgamation of daal.</em>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-672\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Veg_Handi_1600-737x1024.jpg\" alt=\"An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events\" width=\"640\" height=\"889\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>Rice : 3 cups</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil : 1 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Onion (sliced) : 2 medium</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Mutton : 750 gm</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>National Ginger &amp; Garlic Paste : 1 tablespoon each</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Pulao Masala : 1/2 packet</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Carrots (grated) : 1 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Raisins : 2 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Sugar : 2 tablespoons</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Almonds (blanched) : 10</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Pistachios (blanched) : 10</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Wash and soak rice for at least 3 hours and keep changing the water every hour.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>In a large pot, fry the onions till dark brown in color. Strain, crush and keep aside.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>In the same oil add the mutton, National Ginger Paste, and National Garlic Paste. Cook until the meat is slightly brown.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Now add Pulao Masala and 6-7 cups of water; bring to a full boil then turn the heat low and simmer till the meat is tender. If required add Iodized Salt to taste.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>In a small saucepan add carrots, raisins, sugar and 1/2 cup water. Cook on medium heat until the carrots get softened and liquid dries out. Keep aside.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Add crushed fried onions to the mutton gravy that depart a deep caramel flavor and color to the gravy.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When the meat is ready, strain the soaked rice and add to the meat. Cook over a high heat until most of the liquid disappears. You should have enough liquid left to cook rice in. You may add some additional hot water if required.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Turn the heat low.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Serve the pulao with the carrots, and raisins. Generously garnish with blanched almonds and pistachios.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis delicious and extravagant dish is an all-event-purpose dish, however, Afghani pulao tastes best when cooked slow and served hot. We recommend you to make this dish during Aakhd or Mehedi nights with a fewer number of guests as catering this pulao is a complex process and it will require a lot of labor and time to serve a greater number of guests.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Fried Chops Recipe</strong></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-669 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image007-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />Typical chops made special with a unique frying method which will give you a scrumptious meal.</em></p>\r\n<strong><em>Ingredients</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em>chops : 1 kg</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Onions : 2</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Ginger Garlic Paste : 2 teaspoon</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Vinegar : half cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Eggs : 2</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Breadcrumbs : 1 cup</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Oil For frying</em></li>\r\n 	<li><em>Masala : 1 packet (50 grams)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Method</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>In a deep pot, combine the onions, chops, ginger garlic paste, Masala, vinegar and 2 glasses of water.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Set on medium heat to cook.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When the chops are tender, remove them from the pot and let cool.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Dip the cooled chops first in beaten egg, then in breadcrumbs and deep fry to a crispy golden color.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFried Chops are comparatively easy to cook and serve, but it is absolutely necessary that they are freshly fried. Having them fried 2-3 hours before serving will deteriorate its taste and make it look unappealing. Traditionally fried chops are an essential fine-dine menu in Pakistan during the wedding, but we recommend this dish for Aakhd during the winter season.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Source: <a href=\"http://www.madeeasy.com.pk\">www.madeeasy.com.pk</a></em>', 'An Unconventional Dish for indoor wedding events', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '578-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-03 11:24:52', '2019-01-03 11:24:52', '', 578, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2019/01/03/578-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(887, 4, '2019-01-02 12:20:43', '2019-01-02 12:20:43', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The idea behind dressing up for a Bangladeshi wedding ceremony is to dress to look the part of the wedding guest. Since the idea is to blend in with the mass while also making yourself stand out via your sense of style, a simple but elegant dress with non-over-pouring jewelry will make you stand apart among a crowd that is garbed in vibrant celebratory colors.</p>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-3.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"543\" height=\"362\" />\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: MAT Photography</h6>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Never skip jewelry in a Bangladeshi wedding</strong></h3>\r\nA saree or lehenga looks half-finished if not ornamented with the right jewelry. Pick a pair of Dangles or Stud earrings for your ears. And don’t forget to adorn your neck. A meek gold chain with a glistening pendant will be enough to complete your outfit.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-356 \" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-10-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"406\" height=\"608\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:জলছাপ</p>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-347 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-1.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"421\" height=\"632\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Mate</p>\r\n\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Haldi Ceremony</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"wp-image-350 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-4.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"531\" height=\"354\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-346 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/vgsgfvg.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"529\" height=\"352\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\nSince the event consists of you applying turmeric paste on the bride and groom, try to avoid long or over hanging dresses. The more you wear, the harder it will be for you to handle the excessive clothing materials in the midst of the crowd, and more the chances of you staining your precious clothes. A simple kamiz or kurta is enough.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-351 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-5.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"522\" height=\"348\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Photoholic</p>\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n<h3><strong>Wedding Ceremony &amp; Reception</strong></h3>\r\n<strong> </strong>The wedding and reception ceremony is a great time for you to try out various designer wears and the latest trends. However, we ask you to not go over the top in excitement.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, rule out blatantly simple attires like salwars or kurtas. Traditional clothing is the best outfit to garb yourself with as most of our weddings follow the traditional trend. Gowns, trousers, crop-top, skirts or anything too close-fitting or skimpy is a huge NO.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-352 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-6.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"423\" height=\"635\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\nYour best option is to go with a Saree or the second best attire- Lehenga. If you’re a guest at the wedding, don’t wear anything too bright or a saree or lehenga that is covered with embroideries or embellishments.', 'What to wear to a Bangladeshi wedding as a female guest', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '343-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-02 12:20:43', '2019-01-02 12:20:43', '', 343, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2019/01/02/343-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(885, 4, '2019-01-02 12:13:07', '2019-01-02 12:13:07', '<em>In Old Dhaka, kebabs, naans, bakharkhani, kachchi and, haleem, bhuna khichuri, and tehari are found in almost every corner of the street. It is from these areas of Old Dhaka that the tradition of biriyani has spread out among all restaurants in Dhaka city. However, the kachchi biryani is possibly the most lovely and genuine dhakaiya biryani that I have ever tasted. It is so widely appreciated that Kachchi Biriyani has now become an included dish at weddings, parties, and festivities in Bangladesh.</em>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-812\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image005-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" />\r\n<h3>DELICIOUS LAYERS OF MEAT &amp; RICE</h3>\r\nThe term ‘kachchi’ means raw. Referring to the ingredients being cooked raw, in layers, instead of separately adding cooked meat and rice. Layers of meat, rice, and potatoes are infused with delicious blends of fragrant spices to make the kachchi biryani.\r\n\r\nRegardless of whether it is the delicate piece of the mutton, the tater, or the rice itself, every dollop is a heavenly delight.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-813\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image008.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"522\" height=\"327\" />\r\n\r\nKachchi Biriyani takes lesser time to cook too than other traditional biriyani’s. All the ingredients are mixed in layers and then cooked in the oven instead of separately cooking the rice, meat and then mixing all of them.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-811\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"374\" />\r\n<h3>DO IT YOURSELF!</h3>\r\nNewbie Chefs, like myself, can prepare this grand biriyani at home with ease. After mixing all the ingredients, cook the biriyani in the microwave oven for 1.5-2 hrs. Taking it out sooner might leave the meat undercooked. Traditionally, the sealing process of the cooking pot is done with dough. However, using a lid that perfectly fits the cooking pan also gets the job done. Especially if you’re a novice cook, this technique saves you time and causes no muggy fingers.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-820\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Beef-Biryani.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" />\r\n<h3>APPETIZERS AND DESSERTS</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA simple salad of carrots, cucumbers, onions etc- is just enough as a side for kachchi biryani. As an appetizer, you can serve Borhani. For desserts, you can never go wrong with, Mishti bhaat or Morabba- made from chal kumra.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-821\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/pulav_1447762978.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"660\" height=\"370\" /> <img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-822\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/lassi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"537\" /> <img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-823\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/20171220-salted-mint-lassi-borhani-vicky-wasik-11-1500x1125-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nWith time, you will learn to master the art of cooking Kacchi adding a variety of spices and experimenting. Your hard work will be paid off when you gather your family and friends around the dining table. Hear them enjoy and laugh together while savoring each and every bite of the mouthwatering Biryani.\r\n\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n<h3>KACHCHI SPOTS</h3>\r\nIf cooking isn’t your cup of tea, you can still have a mouthful of this delicacy in some popular restaurants. Namely- Al Rajjak, Star Kabab Banani, Fakhruddin, Handi, Sultan Dine’s etc.<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-815\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image010-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>**Pictures taken from the internet</em>', 'THE KACHCHI CULTURE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '572-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-02 12:13:07', '2019-01-02 12:13:07', '', 572, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2019/01/02/572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(883, 4, '2019-01-02 12:12:30', '2019-01-02 12:12:30', '<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-644\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/36410191_1861309160602031_1776284081466638336_n.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/88\">Wedding Moments</a></p>\r\nYour skincare represents a huge part of your wedding look. Obviously, cosmetics and makeup form an important part too, but like everything else, a decent base is the most essential factor in getting an incredible look on your wedding day! Moreover, a good skin is imperative when you’re on your wedding day among hundreds of people and you won\'t have any sort of makeup to put on before getting that exclusive wedding picture.\r\n\r\nSo we have come up with some tips on bridal skincare that you should follow through before your big day!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-649\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/BRIDAL-SKINCARE-2.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/86\">Retro Focus Photography</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Eating right and sleeping on time</strong></h4>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-656\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/lionesse-eat-healthy-for-great-skin-hair-and-nails.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-653\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/gin-and-juice-3-683x1024.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nIt doesn’t matter how much worth of makeup you put on your face, if you don’t eat and sleep right, your make up won’t stand out and do justice for the amount of time and money you would have invested in your cosmetics. For Brides, this might be a tricky routine to follow. The most important practice is to have a good breakfast stacked with organic juices, fruits, and coconut water. Couple that with a minimum of at least 7 hours of uninterrupted sleep truly makes a huge difference on your skin.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-642 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/16991885_802106859938390_6592654392634475891_o-1024x902.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"640\" height=\"564\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/130\">Metro Weddings</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Exfoliating and Masking</strong></h4>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-657\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/ScrubBar2_1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nIf you’re not much of a skincare person or you don’t want to take those extra steps of making a routine sleep and diet, you can start exfoliating and masking. It is a simple technique that is guaranteed to work. Exfoliating at least once a week, cleansing your skin every day and applying sunscreen in moderation will work wonders for your skin. We advise you to use all these creams from the same brand for better results. In addition, masking 3-4 times a week is a must. Keep in mind, if possible use homemade products rather than those ready-made store products. For dry skin, mix olive oil and egg yolk to be put on your skin to give it a glow and try to use the charcoal mask at least once a month.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-662\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/22851728_1893834734266288_7433735531536124747_n-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE FOR THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/94\">Photoholic</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-643\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/31491537_1090873837732192_3238380804035837952_n.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"601\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/89\">Reminiscence Photography</a></p>\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n<h4><strong>Ayurveda for natural skin care treatment</strong></h4>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-658 size-full\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/8-1.png\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"700\" height=\"438\" />\r\n\r\nSwitching to all natural Ayurveda is your best alternative if you don’t want to use the traditional inorganic cosmetic products. Ayurvedic products usually take time to show results. It is advised to start using them at least 6-8 months before your wedding. For best results, slowly cut down fast food or oily food from your daily routine. Even if you do, eat them in moderation. Use vegetable oil if you have to and eating fruits is a must!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-645\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/36532340_1866376746761939_1840891552218480640_n.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/88\">Wedding Moments</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-650\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/BRIDAL-SKINCARE.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/109\">জলছাপ</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Dry Brushing</strong></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-646\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Bella-Nani-Dry-Brushing-1024x855.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"600\" height=\"501\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-651\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Electric-Makeup-Brush-Cleaner-Dryer-Set-Make-Up-Brushes-Washing-Tool-Makeup-Brushes-Cleaner-Dry-In_f18f6857-5629-43ce-94fd-0f6f07410ed2_1024x1024@2x-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nContrary to scientific beliefs, dry brushing has actually helped a lot of people in getting a softer and smoother skin. Even some dermatologists will suggest you try this out. There are a lot of benefits to dry brushing. First, brushing the skin regularly helps stimulate the normal lymph flow under the skin. It helps the body detoxify itself naturally as lymph vessels run under the skin. Second, using a smaller and softer dry brush helps the skin in clearing oil, dirt, and residue from the pores. And third, dry brushing removes dead skins and cells from the surface of the skin and helps reduce cellulite. Find the right brush and use multiple brushes for different parts of your body.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-641 size-large\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/16991743_802107129938363_4561969848663676970_o-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/130\">Metro Weddings</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-648\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/BRIDAL-SKINCARE-1.jpg\" alt=\"BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Credit: <a href=\"https://www.ayojok.com/vendors/photography%20and%20cinematography/108\">MAT Photography</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '550-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-02 12:12:30', '2019-01-02 12:12:30', '', 550, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2019/01/02/550-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
