(825, 4, '2018-11-29 09:03:09', '2018-11-29 09:03:09', '<em>In Old Dhaka, kebabs, naans, bakharkhani, kachchi and, haleem, bhuna khichuri, and tehari are found in almost every corner of the street. It is from these areas of Old Dhaka that the tradition of biriyani has spread out among all restaurants in Dhaka city. However, the kachchi biryani is possibly the most lovely and genuine dhakaiya biryani that I have ever tasted. It is so widely appreciated that Kachchi Biriyani has now become an included dish at weddings, parties, and festivities in Bangladesh.</em>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-812\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image005-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" />\r\n<h3>DELICIOUS LAYERS OF MEAT &amp; RICE</h3>\r\nThe term ‘kachchi’ means raw. Referring to the ingredients being cooked raw, in layers, instead of separately adding cooked meat and rice. Layers of meat, rice, and potatoes are infused with delicious blends of fragrant spices to make the kachchi biryani.\r\n\r\nRegardless of whether it is the delicate piece of the mutton, the tater, or the rice itself, every dollop is a heavenly delight.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-813\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image008.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"522\" height=\"327\" />\r\n\r\nKachchi Biriyani takes lesser time to cook too than other traditional biriyani’s. All the ingredients are mixed in layers and then cooked in the oven instead of separately cooking the rice, meat and then mixing all of them.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-811\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"374\" />\r\n<h3>DO IT YOURSELF!</h3>\r\nNewbie Chefs, like myself, can prepare this grand biriyani at home with ease. After mixing all the ingredients, cook the biriyani in the microwave oven for 1.5-2 hrs. Taking it out sooner might leave the meat undercooked. Traditionally, the sealing process of the cooking pot is done with dough. However, using a lid that perfectly fits the cooking pan also gets the job done. Especially if you’re a novice cook, this technique saves you time and causes no muggy fingers.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-820\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Beef-Biryani.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" />\r\n<h3>APPETIZERS AND DESSERTS</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA simple salad of carrots, cucumbers, onions etc- is just enough as a side for kachchi biryani. As an appetizer, you can serve Borhani. For desserts, you can never go wrong with, Mishti bhaat or Morabba- made from chal kumra.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-821\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/pulav_1447762978.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"660\" height=\"370\" /> <img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-822\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/lassi.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"537\" /> <img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-823\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/20171220-salted-mint-lassi-borhani-vicky-wasik-11-1500x1125-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nWith time, you will learn to master the art of cooking Kacchi adding a variety of spices and experimenting. Your hard work will be paid off when you gather your family and friends around the dining table. Hear them enjoy and laugh together while savoring each and every bite of the mouthwatering Biryani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>KACHCHI SPOTS</h3>\r\nIf cooking isn’t your cup of tea, you can still have a mouthful of this delicacy in some popular restaurants. Namely- Al Rajjak, Star Kabab Banani, Fakhruddin, Handi, Sultan Dine’s etc.<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-815\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/image010-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>**Pictures taken from the internet</em>', 'THE KACHCHI CULTURE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '572-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-29 09:03:09', '2018-11-29 09:03:09', '', 572, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/11/29/572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
