(523, 4, '2018-10-17 05:54:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'We know if given the opportunity, you would take every chance to make your wedding events stand out from the rest. Who does not want their wedding to be unique and different and attract all the attention? Therefore, we have come up with 4 OUT-OF-THE-BOX themes that you can apply to your own wedding!\r\n<h3><strong>Indoor Garden</strong></h3>\r\nThe theme is best suited for the summer season. The look will definitely brighten up and give a more natural atmosphere with a smell of freshness to indoor venues with zero natural beauty. Covering the walls in green leaves, small plants spread throughout the corners with suspending lanterns, while fencing the dinner area with green hanging chandeliers. Turn your experience of a closed banquet hall into a sensation of being outdoors.\r\n<h3><strong>Vintage</strong></h3>\r\nVintage will never go out of style. This theme will set a classy and elegant mood throughout the event. Wishy-washy colors, lots of antique showpieces, mirrors, white pearls used instead of flowers to decorate table tops, and lots of white candles. For extra mood setting, use English teacups as centerpieces for tables.\r\nFor extra mood setting, you can take all your pictures in black and white or in a specific retro filter.\r\n<h3><strong>Glamor</strong></h3>\r\nThe theme should be black and gold/white themed event. However, for absolute aesthetics, the guests need to be dressed in black and gold/white too. Although this seems like a tremendous task to ask your guests to dress to complement the theme, we can’t help but admire how beautiful it looks. It is necessary to address the fact that this is best suited for Engagement or Anniversary events. Again, Lots of candles are required and red roses are thrown around to give a contrast. Use Black and Gold helium balloons to cover corners of the ceilings. Curtain an entire wall with strings attached with bulbs.\r\n<h3><strong>Paper Origami</strong></h3>\r\nThis theme is Ideal for the Mehendi nights or Sangeet Nights. Using paper might sound very simplistic, However, it is very economical but still gives a beautiful artistry to your event. Swapping real flowers for paper flowers on the tables, hanging bright origami cranes from the ceiling instead of flowers or chandeliers, and using large floral ribbons to curtain a wall-making the picture-perfect background for your photo booth. Use paper flowers in steel pots as centerpieces. What’s beautiful about this theme is, you can engage your relatives and little cousins in making and decorating origamis so that everyone feels included.', '4 OUT-OF-THE-BOX Themes for Wedding events', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2018-10-17 05:54:58', '2018-10-17 05:54:58', '', 0, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/?p=523', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(619, 4, '2018-10-22 07:42:14', '2018-10-22 07:42:14', '<em>In Old Dhaka, kebabs, naans, bakharkhani, kachchi and, haleem, bhuna khichuri, and tehari are found in almost every corner of the street. It is from these areas of Old Dhaka that the tradition of biriyani has spread out among all restaurants in Dhaka city. However, the kachchi biryani is possibly the most lovely and genuine dhakaiya biryani that I have ever tasted. It is so widely appreciated that Kachchi Biriyani has now become an included dish at weddings, parties, and festivities in Bangladesh.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>DELICIOUS LAYERS OF MEAT &amp; RICE</h3>\r\nThe term ‘kachchi’ means raw. Referring to the ingredients being cooked raw, in layers, instead of separately adding cooked meat and rice. Layers of meat, rice, and potatoes are infused with delicious blends of fragrant spices to make the kachchi biryani.\r\n\r\nRegardless of whether it is the delicate piece of the mutton, the tater, or the rice itself, every dollop is a heavenly delight.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKachchi Biriyani takes lesser time to cook too than other traditional biriyani’s. All the ingredients are mixed in layers and then cooked in the oven instead of separately cooking the rice, meat and then mixing all of them.\r\n\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n<h3>DO IT YOURSELF!</h3>\r\nNewbie Chefs, like myself, can prepare this grand biriyani at home with ease. After mixing all the ingredients, cook the biriyani in the microwave oven for 1.5-2 hrs. Taking it out sooner might leave the meat undercooked. Traditionally, the sealing process of the cooking pot is done with dough. However, using a lid that perfectly fits the cooking pan also gets the job done. Especially if you’re a novice cook, this technique saves you time and causes no muggy fingers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>APPETIZERS AND DESSERTS</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA simple salad of carrots, cucumbers, onions etc- is just enough as a side for kachchi biryani. As an appetizer, you can serve Borhani. For desserts, you can never go wrong with Morabba- made from chal kumra.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith time, you will learn to master the art of cooking Kacchi adding a variety of spices and experimenting. Your hard work will be paid off when you gather your family and friends around the dining table. Hear them enjoy and laugh together while savoring each and every bite of the mouthwatering Biryani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>KACHCHI SPOTS</h3>\r\nIf cooking isn’t your cup of tea, you can still have a mouthful of this delicacy in some popular restaurants. Namely- Al Rajjak, Star Kabab Banani, Fakhruddin, Handi, Sultan Dine’s etc.', 'THE KACHCHI CULTURE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '572-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-22 07:42:14', '2018-10-22 07:42:14', '', 572, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/22/572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
