f flowers you will use to make the crown and moreover, this will create a whole new theme for your event with an extra touch of personalization. The bravura of the crown can vary from rustic to fanciful.\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n\r\n \r\nTHE HOLI COLORS\r\nWhether you use holi colors for pre-wedding or post-wedding, the pictures that will come out will look absolutely stunning and fun. You get to have fun throwing all these colors at your friends and cousins while having all those intimate moments captured in colors- inevitably will make you come back to these photos and relive those moments from time to time. Find an outdoor place, or book a resort if you have to. Wear all white for better color contrast pictures.\r\n', '4 unique and trending Photography themes for your wedding!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '526-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-15 06:28:34', '2018-10-15 06:28:34', '', 526, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/15/526-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(529, 4, '2018-10-15 07:10:25', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'If you’re a Bengali, Holud is probably a more significant affair to you than your wedding day.\r\nAn event- where you get to perform fun yet silly looking choreographed dance routines along with your cousins and friends, while later going off at some traditional Bangla music performed by a generic band or banging your head to some sweet EDM performed by a DJ,- will always be unforgettable. You may feel somewhat intimidated realizing that you need to organize Holud decor designs without anyone else, due to expensive billings, or you might be one of those individuals who loves producing self-crafted art so that it gives you a sense of memorability on your Holud night. Whatever the reasons are, these five DIY Holud decors will enable you to make your day more cherished by engaging yourself more into your once in a lifetime event.\r\n<h5><strong>1. Origami Decors</strong></h5>\r\nAll you need are some glazed papers or just colored papers along with a thread to hang them around the venue. Wondering how to make them? Watch some YouTube videos on how to make them. In fact, it’s so easy that even your 10-year-old niece can do it. (Sit with your F&amp;F and make them with fun &amp; gossip)\r\nAn easy tutorial on how to make paper origami-\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KfnyopxdJXQ\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KfnyopxdJXQ</a>\r\n\r\nSource: <a href=\"http://www.blingsparkle.com/2016/03/5-amazing-diy-decor-ideas-for-your.html\">http://www.blingsparkle.com/2016/03/5-amazing-diy-decor-ideas-for-your.html</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5><strong>2. Holud paper fans</strong></h5>\r\nThey are the easiest of them all. Just pick two pop colors such as bright yellow and baby blue or pink and orange. Stick these on the entrance of the venue or around the stage. Having the right combination of colors is important. You don’t want your decorations to turn out dull and boring! So use proper color contrasts and make it flamboyant.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5><strong>3. The curtains of Dupatta</strong></h5>\r\nFreely hang the flowy dupattas against the windows and at the back of your couch against the wall. Additionally, wrap these as \'throws\' over your couch. Strew cushion covers all around the floor in different aesthetic formations. Use mirrored walls from as a source of better light popping impressions.\r\nAttach few colored ribbons and voila! You have a colorfully simple yet professional looking garlands at your place.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5><strong>4. Paper kites and lamps/lanterns</strong></h5>\r\nThread multiple kites on a string and throw it around your living room or decorated lawn making sure that the kites appear like they are suspended in the air. In addition, you can hang around paper lamps or lanterns alongside the kites in various color contrast combinations to make them look lively.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5><strong>5. Colorful umbrellas</strong></h5>\r\nThe DIY decor below might look complicated and tough but in actuality, it\'s very easy to make. All you have to do is find a way to clasp the umbrellas in place and stitch flowers like tufts around it. Get artistic and droop something else in place of the flower strings like bangle tassels or beaded chains. To make it look more extra artistic, place a photo booth in the midst of all these decorations.\r\n\r\nAll the decors listed above can be self-made and can be found at a reasonable price in places like Chandi Chawk, New Market, Shahbag, Elephant Road, Chawkbazar etc.', '5 DIY HOLUD DECORS', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2018-10-15 07:10:25', '2018-10-15 07:10:25', '', 0, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/?p=529', 0, 'post', '', 0),
