(541, 4, '2018-10-15 08:05:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Dark circles around the eyes can stress you out especially if you are a bride to be and your wedding day is just around the corner. But fear not, there is always a solution to any mighty problems in the world and dark circles are of no matter. A lot can be done by the brides to revive that glow on your face- from having a balanced diet to having adequate amounts of sleep. Let’s take a look at such 6 super easy tricks to remove the dark circles from your exhausted eyes.\r\n<h4>Eat healthy</h4>\r\nA balanced diet is key to a healthy skin. What you eat is reflected upon your face. Eating more junk will result in pimples and high blood pressure. These usually lead to dark circles. So avoid oily foods at all costs and start eating healthy. Fresh vegetables, clean meat for protein, organic juices for vitamins and drink a lot of water to stay hydrated. Notice the changes in just a few weeks.\r\n<h4>Proper amount of sleep</h4>\r\nWe know weddings are stressful and you need to deal with a lot of problems and issues. But never put sleep as your second priority. Having an adequate amount of sleep is so essential for the skin. Lack of sleep not only produces dark circles, but it generates other skin and health problems too. So, don’t ever compromise your sleep over anything else.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Aloe Vera- a miracle against dark circles</h4>\r\nWhen you can’t find anything else, try your favorite aloe gel. It’s the ultimate solution to almost all your skincare problems. It contains vitamin-e oils and nourishing properties that can help reduce puffiness under your eyes. All you have to do is not skip and keep trying it religiously for a week.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Wash your makeup</h4>\r\nNever, under any circumstances, go to sleep with your makeup on. Cosmetic products are not meant to be worn all day. If your makeup stays on your skin for too long, it clogs the pores on your skin making your eyes puffier and bumpier. No matter how tired you are, always remember to wash off and clean your make before going to bed.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Gentle oil massage</h4>\r\nMix some almond oil and coconut oil in a bowl. Put some of the mixture on your fingers and gently massage it underneath and above your eyes. Do this every night for at least two weeks to see any results. This oil mixture is rich in Vitamin E and Vitamin K and acts as a very good moisturizer for the skin and helps in removing pesky dark circles.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4>Ice packs</h4>\r\nA nice ice pack can give your eyes just the right relief it needs by minimizing the inflammation of the blood vessels. Take some dry ice cubes and wrap them inside a piece of cloth. Gently dab the ice pack under your eyes. Don’t apply too much as the areas around the eyes are very sensitive.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '6 Super easy Tricks to Remove Dark Circles Days before your Wedding', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'open', '', 'remove-dark-circles', '', '', '2018-10-15 08:05:31', '2018-10-15 08:05:31', '', 0, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/?p=541', 0, 'post', '', 0),
