(547, 4, '2018-10-15 08:23:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'The best kind of advice, guidance, and moral support are provided by our friends all throughout our life. For any obstacles or bumps along our life, more often than not, we look up to our best friends for solutions. So what about your best friend on her wedding day? Being a bride is not as cheerful as you might think. She has to go under a lot of stress, has inadequate sleep, maintains a strict schedule and that too with mood swings. It is absolutely necessary that the bride has her best friends around her to give her invaluable moral support to tame her stress and mood swings. Here are 8 unsaid duties of every bride’s friend to level up your games:\r\n<h3><strong>The fashion advisor</strong>.</h3>\r\nSelecting the perfect dress to look beautiful on the big day is every bride’s desire, but the actual process of choosing the dress, picking the right color, matching outfits with the theme can make a bride worried and confused. Always be prepared to help her come to a decision while choosing the dress. Don’t confuse her too much with too many options.\r\n<h3><strong>Makeup</strong>.</h3>\r\nGo to the beauty salon with the bride to make sure the beauticians are doing exactly what the bride wanted. Make sure you assist her in wearing saree or lehenga. Also, keep track of time to fit everything into the schedule.\r\n<h3><strong>Bathroom breaks</strong>.</h3>\r\nThe bride’s dress is usually heavy and intricate. It gets in the way of her movement which causes a huge struggle sometimes. So help the bride in dragging this bulky outfit to the bathroom if needed. Wherever the bride goes, you go too.\r\n<h3><strong>Gossip Girls</strong>.</h3>\r\nUse your clever social skills to find out what relatives or aunties are saying about you, your dress, the food, the event. If you get a negative vibe from them, pass on some sweet words for the bride to leave a good impression. Later in the day, talk about all the gossips with the bride and have a laugh.\r\n<h3><strong>The Comedian</strong>.</h3>\r\nIt is very tiresome and boring for the bride to sit in one place for the entirety of the event. Cheer her up every now and then to let go of her tension and boredom. Crack some jokes to lighten her mood and keep her entertained.\r\n<h3><strong>Help her at the table.</strong></h3>\r\nHelp her eat without spilling it on her dress. Fold her lehenga or saree if needed, help her sit down at the table. During indoor events, if possible, feed her.\r\n<h3><strong>Goodbyes are hard</strong>.</h3>\r\nThe end of every wedding is emotional and sad, especially for the bride who most likely has to move away from her parent’s house to start a new life. Help her get through those emotional goodbyes by giving her moral support. Wipe away those tears without ruining her makeup and make sure you hug her during those emotional moments. Also, keep an eye out for the bride’s mother. Her mother needs as much emotional support as the bride during this time.\r\n<h3><strong>Visit the bride at her new home</strong>.</h3>\r\nDon’t think that just because the wedding ceremony is over, so does your responsibility towards the bride. She needs you more than ever now that she has to adjust to a new life at her in-laws. Visit her every now and then, give her advice, and bring her gifts or her favorite dessert. Keep her accompanied whenever you can and build a good relationship with her in-laws. In that way, she will get more accustomed to the new environment and feel more at home.', '8 unsaid duties of every bride ’s friend', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'open', '', '8-unsaid-duties-every-bride-s-friend', '', '', '2018-10-15 08:23:28', '2018-10-15 08:23:28', '', 0, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/?p=547', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(548, 4, '2018-10-15 08:16:55', '2018-10-15 08:16:55', 'Each and every one of us needs a compliment on our wedding day. Since the wedding day is one of the greatest days for both bride and groom, looking good will always make you feel good on your big day. Especially for the ladies, they have always been intrigued and conscious about their looks around this extraordinary day. It is only in this day that brides get to be a princess and a queen at the same time.\r\n\r\nSo here are some small recommendations on how to look great on your wedding day:\r\n\r\n<strong>Plan your outfit: </strong>\r\n\r\nIt is vital to decide and finalize what you will be wearing on your wedding day at least four months before. Research online on what kind of outfits are trendy and upcoming. Try to complement your wedding outfit with the theme of your wedding, if you have one. It is absolutely vital that the dress that you will be wearing is fitted to your desire. So visit the tailor every now and then to check your fitting in case there aren’t any mishaps. And even if there is, you will have enough time to correct your outfit.\r\n<h5><strong>Assign your Makeup Artist: </strong></h5>\r\nIt is one of the key issues to decide on your makeup artist as soon as possible, at least a month before the wedding day. It is imperative for the ladies to choose their makeup artist much earlier because most of the time makeup artists have a long list of appointments so it gets very hard to find a free schedule of your favorite makeup artist. Your makeup artist is the main magician who can make you look prettier and more beautiful. So avoid any issues by booking them early.\r\n<h5><strong>Pick your shoes:</strong></h5>\r\nYour shoe matter as much as your outfits. In fact, finding the right pair of shoes is harder than choosing your outfit. A perfect pair of footwear that matches your dress will elevate the beauty and handsomeness of both the bride and groom significantly. Schedule a day for footwear shopping, at least one month before your wedding.\r\n<h5><strong>Jewelry:</strong></h5>\r\n<h5>Jewelry simply comes down to personal preferences. You might the type of person who wants to garb themselves with gold or you might be someone who prefers minimalistic jewelry as simple as floral ornaments. Whatever your preferences are, make sure you have fixed your budget for jewelry before going out shopping. Do some proper research on the market value of gold and diamond. Find out which shops have your preferred designs. If you are going for custom jewelry, talk to your designer months before the wedding for better results as custom jewelry need to be fitted perfectly. So some time for trial and error is needed.</h5>\r\n<h5><strong>Grooming:</strong></h5>\r\nBoth the bride and groom should start taking care of themselves at least 3 months before their wedding. Follow a routine balanced diet. If possible, join a gym or a yoga class to keep your body in shape. Most importantly start taking care of your skin. Avoid oily junk foods and start consuming fresh vegetables and organic juices. Rather than using cosmetic items to take care of your skin, use herbal or homemade products. Exfoliation also helps regenerate the glow on your face. And last but not the least, get adequate amount of sleep of at least up to 8 hours.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5><strong>Stop being stressed:</strong></h5>\r\nIt is important to stay relaxed and tension free during the wedding day. Stress leads to higher blood pressure and that is bad both emotionally and physically. Your anxiety will start to manifest on your face and degrade your look. Avoid conflicts during the wedding day, let your friends and family do the small tasks that are required. It is okay to give up control on certain trivial decisions that will take up an unnecessary amount of your time. So chill out, stay back and relax at your home until the bigger task that requires your attention unfolds. Chat with friends, watch some tv and most of all stay hydrated.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '6 ways to look great at your wedding', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '544-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-15 08:16:55', '2018-10-15 08:16:55', '', 544, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/15/544-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
