(553, 4, '2018-10-15 11:26:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<em>There is something that\'s just so much fun about taking photos with friends, cousins or families especially with some added props and a cool background to make an interesting photo booth. This makes a more interesting and cooler set of pictures that you can preserve and have a laugh on or smile as you go through your photo albums years later. So here are 4 DIY photo booths that are inexpensive and will look amazing at the same time.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong><em>A Couch, an Adorable Quote, and Some Chaplet</em></strong></h4>\r\nPlace a sofa (preferably of a color that goes with the event theme) against one of the walls in the room- look for a space that is empty, well-lit and close to the entrance. Include a few embellishments to make it pop up. Use paper cut letters as the quote and cover the wall with origami or fairy lights OR use flowers to make a beautiful backdrop for this photo booth.\r\n\r\n<em>Purchasing source: you can use a used sofa or search in online selling websites for a used couch at a cheap price. You can find hanging alphabets in any gift shops.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n<h3><strong><em>HANGING GREENERY     </em></strong></h3>\r\nDIY tips: Construct a hanger using wood or metal, or you can use your wardrobe hanger. Make a few leafy branches and hang them over the hanger however you like. You can go a step further by hanging simple garlands made of leaves. Make sure you place the hanger against a dark colored wall to give a better contrast for your photo booth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Purchasing source: flower shops in Shahbag, wooden hangar from Badda.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong><em>Giant Oversized Frame</em></strong></h3>\r\nDIY Tips: This oversized frame photo booth is relatively simple to make. It can made using a cardboard or foam. If you don’t have room or space to set aside a whole area for the photo booth, it can easily be carried around, but at the same time, it will as a backdrop as well.\r\n\r\n<em>Purchasing source: Any stationary shops sells cardboards and foams </em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\r\n<h3><strong><em>Make Your Own Props</em></strong></h3>\r\n<em>Source: <a href=\"http://www.wedmegood.com\">www.wedmegood.com</a></em>\r\n\r\nDIY Tips: If buying props for photo booths is too much of a hassle for you, then simply make your own! Click <a href=\"https://somethingturquoise.com/2015/02/10/diy-free-photo-booth-stick-props/\">here</a> for a tutorial to make props like these on your own. Once you have these, guests won’t care about a backdrop. But if you do want one, hang up a glittery or colorful sheet.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><strong><em>Unique and Sole Photo booth</em></strong></h3>\r\nDIY Tips: This depends solely upon the bride and groom. If you have a cool idea of how your photo booth is going to be, then talk to your friends, partner and decorator to see whether that’s implementable. You can search online for various types of unique photo booths to get an idea.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'DIY Photo booth', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'open', '', 'diy-photo-booth', '', '', '2018-10-15 11:26:44', '2018-10-15 11:26:44', '', 0, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/?p=553', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(554, 4, '2018-10-15 08:46:30', '2018-10-15 08:46:30', 'Your skin represents a huge part of your wedding look. Obviously, cosmetics and makeup form an important part too, but like everything else, a decent base is the most essential factor in getting an incredible look on your wedding day! Moreover, a good skin is imperative when you’re on your wedding day among hundreds of people and you won\'t have any sort of makeup to put on before getting that exclusive wedding picture.\r\n\r\nSo we have come up with some tips on bridal skincare that you should follow through before your big day!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Eating right and sleeping on time</strong></h4>\r\nIt doesn’t matter how much worth of makeup you put on your face, if you don’t eat and sleep right, your make up won’t stand out and do justice for the amount of time and money you would have invested in your cosmetics. For Brides, this might be a tricky routine to follow. The most important practice is to have a good breakfast stacked with organic juices, fruits, and coconut water. Couple that with a minimum of at least 7 hours of uninterrupted sleep truly makes a hug difference on your skin.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Exfoliating and Masking</strong></h4>\r\nIf you’re not much of a skincare person or you don’t want to take those extra steps of making a routine sleep and diet, you can start exfoliating and masking. It is a simple technique that is guaranteed to work. Exfoliating at least once a week, cleansing your skin every day and applying sunscreen in moderation will work wonders for your skin. We advise you to use all these creams from the same brand for better results. In addition, masking 3-4 times a week is a must. Keep in mind, if possible use homemade products rather than those ready-made store products. For dry skin, mix olive oil and egg yolk to be put on your skin to give it a glow and try to use the charcoal mask at least once a month.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>All natural Ayurveda</strong></h4>\r\nSwitching to all natural ayurveda is your best alternative if you don’t want to use the traditional inorganic cosmetic products. Ayurvedic products usually take time to show results. It is advised to start using them at least 6-8 months before your wedding. For best results, slowly cut down fast food or oily food from your daily routine. Even if you do, eat them in moderation. Use vegetable oil if you have to and eating fruits is a must!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>Dry Brushing</strong></h4>\r\nContrary to scientific beliefs, dry brushing has actually helped a lot of people in getting a softer and smoother skin. Even some dermatologists will suggest you to try this out. There are a lot of benefits to dry brushing. First, brushing the skin regularly helps stimulate the normal lymph flow under the skin. It helps the body detoxify itself naturally as lymph vessels run under the skin. Second, using a smaller and softer dry brush helps the skin in clearing oil, dirt, and residue from the pores. And third, dry brushing removes dead skins and cells from the surface of the skin and helps reduce cellulite. Find the right brush and use multiple brushes for different parts of your body.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'BRIDAL SKINCARE BEFORE THE WEDDING', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '550-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-15 08:46:30', '2018-10-15 08:46:30', '', 550, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/15/550-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
