(601, 4, '2018-10-17 06:07:17', '2018-10-17 06:07:17', 'If you are looking to spend a good time with your partner, but the budget is the only thing that holds you back, here is an opportunity for you to visit 4 of the best unique Asian honeymoon destinations at a much lesser cost.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>VIETNAM</strong></h4>\r\nVietnam is a Southeast Asian country best known for its wonderful tranquil beaches, gushing rivers, and bustling cities. There is so much to explore in the country as you take a trip to one of the best honeymoon destinations on a budget.\r\n\r\nThings to do: As a couple, you can really enjoy your best moments together here in Vietnam. Some of the best things to do in Vietnam include eating out Vietnamese noodles in a restaurant, cruising in Mekong Delta, crawling via cu chi tunnels or undertake a kayaking or biking trip with the locals.\r\n\r\nA 3 day stay in Vietnam would cost around 40k-50k BDT including plane fare.\r\n\r\nBest time to visit: Between September- December.\r\n\r\nVisa: Visa is required; may be obtained on arrival if prior online approval has been obtained through a travel agency\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>CAMBODIA</strong></h4>\r\nCambodia is another wonderful honeymoon destination in Asia which helps young couples escape the world and to enjoy their new life in their budget. This is one of the cheap honeymoon destinations in the world where you can get the most out of every penny spent, the natural beauty and heritage beauty act as magnets for people around the world.\r\n\r\nThings to do: If you want to explore a new sort of nature on your Southeast Asia honeymoon, this place is a perfect one for you. Cambodia offers you a scenic view of lots of enthralling lakes, Angkor Wat Complex, The Bayon and much more.\r\n\r\nA 3-day stay would cost around BDT 45k-50k BDT including plane fare\r\n\r\nBest time to visit: October to May\r\n\r\nVisa: Visa on arrival for 30 days\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>LAOS</strong></h4>\r\nLaos is truly considered as one of the most colorful honeymoon destinations in Asia and is a must-visit destination in Asia for the lovebirds after their marriage. A place they can happily enjoy their new day of life with full excitement and splendor.\r\n\r\nThings to do: With truly gracious residents, Laos, a wonderful destination is combined with impressive Buddhist temples and shrines, lots of places of interest and mysterious heritage sites as well. It is an idyllic honeymoon getaway for the culture lovers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA 3-4 days stay will cost around BDT 50-55k\r\n\r\nWhen to visit: All the year round\r\n\r\nVisa: Visa on arrival for 30 days.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><strong>KASHMIR</strong></h4>\r\nFrailty that prevails in the valley of Kashmir often disheartens those with humble hearts; yet, Kashmir gives you millions of reasons to celebrate its existence. A picture perfect scene with snow clad mountains, sparkling lakes with sailing shikaras. A tuft of colorful tulips and steady houseboats inflate lungs of the onlookers. Kashmir, the northwestern province of the Indian subcontinent renders the opportunity to experience the onrush of scenery closely.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA 5-6 days tour starting from Dhaka to Kolkata by Air, overnight train From Kolkata to Delhi, and then a flight to Srinagar, Kashmir.\r\n\r\nTotal cost (inclusive of round-trip airfare and train fare cost, food, lodging and sightseeing with a local tourist guide) is around 55k BDT per person.\r\n\r\nMust visit places: Gurez Valley, Gulmarg, Amarnath Yatra- Pahalgam, ancient silk road-Sonmarg.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Reference: <a href=\"http://traveltriangle.com/blog/budget-honeymoon-destinations-in-asia/\">http://traveltriangle.com/blog/budget-honeymoon-destinations-in-asia/</a></em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Economic Honeymoon Destinations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '557-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-17 06:07:17', '2018-10-17 06:07:17', '', 557, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/17/557-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
