(618, 4, '2018-10-18 11:30:51', '2018-10-18 11:30:51', '<em>In Old Dhaka, kebabs, naans, bakharkhani, kachchi and, haleem, bhuna khichuri, and tehari are found in almost every corner of the street. It is from these areas of Old Dhaka that the tradition of biriyani has spread out among all restaurants in Dhaka city. However, the kachchi biryani is possibly the most lovely and genuine dhakaiya biryani that I have ever tasted. It is so widely appreciated that Kachchi Biriyani has now become an included dish at weddings, parties, and festivities in Bangladesh.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>DELICIOUS LAYERS OF MEAT &amp; RICE</h3>\r\nThe term ‘kachchi’ means raw. Referring to the ingredients being cooked raw, in layers, instead of separately adding cooked meat and rice. Layers of meat, rice, and potatoes are infused with delicious blends of fragrant spices to make the kachchi biryani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRegardless of whether it is the delicate piece of the mutton, the tater, or the rice itself, every dollop is a heavenly delight.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKachchi Biriyani takes lesser time to cook too than other traditional biriyani’s. All the ingredients are mixed in layers and then cooked in the oven instead of separately cooking the rice, meat and then mixing all of them.\r\n\r\n[carousel_slide id=\'605\']\r\n<h3>DO IT YOURSELF!</h3>\r\nNewbie Chefs, like myself, can prepare this grand biriyani at home with ease. After mixing all the ingredients, cook the biriyani in the microwave oven for 1.5-2 hrs. Taking it out sooner might leave the meat undercooked. Traditionally, the sealing process of the cooking pot is done with dough. However, using a lid that perfectly fits the cooking pan also gets the job done. Especially if you’re a novice cook, this technique saves you time and causes no muggy fingers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>APPETIZERS AND DESSERTS</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA simple salad of carrots, cucumbers, onions etc- is just enough as a side for kachchi biryani. As an appetizer, you can serve Borhani. For desserts, you can never go wrong with Morabba- made from chal kumra.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith time, you will learn to master the art of cooking Kacchi adding a variety of spices and experimenting. Your hard work will be paid off when you gather your family and friends around the dining table. Hear them enjoy and laugh together while savoring each and every bite of the mouthwatering Biryani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>KACHCHI SPOTS</h3>\r\nIf cooking isn’t your cup of tea, you can still have a mouthful of this delicacy in some popular restaurants. Namely- Al Rajjak, Star Kabab Banani, Fakhruddin, Handi, Sultan Dine’s etc.', 'THE KACHCHI CULTURE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '572-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-18 11:30:51', '2018-10-18 11:30:51', '', 572, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/18/572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(609, 4, '2018-10-17 08:36:49', '2018-10-17 08:36:49', '<em>In Old Dhaka, kebabs, naans, bakharkhani, kachchi and, haleem, bhuna khichuri, and tehari are found in almost every corner of the street. It is from these areas of Old Dhaka that the tradition of biriyani has spread out among all restaurants in Dhaka city. However, the kachchi biryani is possibly the most lovely and genuine dhakaiya biryani that I have ever tasted. It is so widely appreciated that Kachchi Biriyani has now become an included dish at weddings, parties, and festivities in Bangladesh.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>DELICIOUS LAYERS OF MEAT &amp; RICE</h3>\r\nThe term ‘kachchi’ means raw, referring to the ingredients being cooked raw, in layers, instead of separately adding cooked meat and rice, as is the case with some other varieties of biryani. Layers of meat, rice, and potatoes are infused with delicious blends of fragrant spices to make the kachchi biryani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRegardless of whether it is the delicate piece of the mutton, the tater, or the rice itself, every dollop is a heavenly delight.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKachchi Biriyani takes lesser time to cook too than other traditional biriyani’s. All the ingredients are mixed in layers and then cooked in the oven instead of separately cooking the rice, meat and then mixing all of them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>DO IT YOURSELF!</h3>\r\nNewbie Chefs, like myself, can prepare this grand biriyani at home with ease. After mixing all the ingredients, cook the biriyani in the microwave oven for 1.5-2 hrs. Taking it out sooner might leave the meat undercooked. Traditionally, the sealing process of the cooking pot is done with dough. However, using a lid that perfectly fits the cooking pan also gets the job done. Especially if you’re a novice cook, this technique saves you time and causes no muggy fingers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>APPETIZERS AND DESSERTS</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA simple salad of carrots, cucumbers, onions etc- is just enough as a side for kachchi biryani. As an appetizer, you can serve Borhani. For desserts, you can never go wrong with Morabba- made from chal kumra.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith time, you will learn to master the art of cooking Kacchi adding a variety of spices and experimenting. Your hard work will be paid off when you gather your family and friends around the dining table. Hear them enjoy and laugh together while savoring each and every bite of the mouthwatering Biryani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>KACHCHI SPOTS</h3>\r\nIf cooking isn’t your cup of tea, you can still have a mouthful of this delicacy in some popular restaurants. Namely- Al Rajjak, Star Kabab Banani, Fakhruddin, Handi, Sultan Dine’s etc.', 'THE KACHCHI CULTURE', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '572-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-17 08:36:49', '2018-10-17 08:36:49', '', 572, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/17/572-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(610, 4, '2018-10-17 08:54:22', '2018-10-17 08:54:22', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The idea behind dressing up for a Bangladeshi wedding ceremony is to dress to look the part of the wedding guest. Since the idea is to blend in with the mass while also making yourself stand out via your sense of style, a simple but elegant dress with non-over-pouring jewelry will make you stand apart among a crowd that is garbed in vibrant celebratory colors.</p>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-3.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"543\" height=\"362\" />\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: MAT Photography</h6>\r\n[su_carousel source=\"media: 459,461,460,468,467,466,465,464,463,462\" link=\"custom\" target=\"blank\" items=\"5\"]\r\n<h3><strong>Never skip jewelry in a Bangladeshi wedding</strong></h3>\r\nA saree or lehenga looks half-finished if not ornamented with the right jewelry. Pick a pair of Dangles or Stud earrings for your ears. And don’t forget to adorn your neck. A meek gold chain with a glistening pendant will be enough to complete your outfit.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-356 \" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-10-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"406\" height=\"608\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:জলছাপ</p>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-347 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-1.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"421\" height=\"632\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Mate</p>\r\n\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Haldi Ceremony</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"wp-image-350 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-4.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"531\" height=\"354\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-346 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/vgsgfvg.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"529\" height=\"352\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\nSince the event consists of you applying turmeric paste on the bride and groom, try to avoid long or over hanging dresses. The more you wear, the harder it will be for you to handle the excessive clothing materials in the midst of the crowd, and more the chances of you staining your precious clothes. A simple kamiz or kurta is enough.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-351 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-5.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"522\" height=\"348\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Photoholic</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Wedding Ceremony &amp; Reception</strong></h3>\r\n<strong> </strong>The wedding and reception ceremony is a great time for you to try out various designer wears and the latest trends. However, we ask you to not go over the top in excitement.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, rule out blatantly simple attires like salwars or kurtas. Traditional clothing is the best outfit to garb yourself with as most of our weddings follow the traditional trend. Gowns, trousers, crop-top, skirts or anything too close-fitting or skimpy is a huge NO.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-352 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-6.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"423\" height=\"635\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\nYour best option is to go with a Saree or the second best attire- Lehenga. If you’re a guest at the wedding, don’t wear anything too bright or a saree or lehenga that is covered with embroideries or embellishments.', 'What to wear to a Bangladeshi wedding as a female guest', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '343-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-17 08:54:22', '2018-10-17 08:54:22', '', 343, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/17/343-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
