(359, 3, '2018-09-30 11:44:59', '2018-09-30 11:44:59', 'The idea behind dressing up for a Bangladeshi wedding ceremony is to dress to look the part of the wedding guest. Since the idea is to blend in with the mass while also making yourself stand out via your sense of style, a simple but elegant dress with non-over-pouring jewelry will make you stand apart among a crowd that is garbed in vibrant celebratory colors.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-349\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-3.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"1840\" height=\"1228\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Don’t Skip Jewelry</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA saree or a lehenga looks half-finished if not ornamented with the right jewelry. Pick a pair of Dangles or Stud earrings for your ears. And don’t forget to adorn your neck. A meek gold chain with a glistening pendant will be enough to complete your outfit.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-356\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-10.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-347\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-1.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"1365\" height=\"2048\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Haldi Ceremony</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-355\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-9.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-346\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/vgsgfvg.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"468\" height=\"312\" />\r\n\r\nSince the event consists of you applying turmeric paste on the bride and groom, try to avoid long or over hanging dresses. The more you wear, the harder it will be for you to handle the excessive clothing materials in the midst of the crowd, and more the chances of you staining your precious clothes. A simple kamiz or kurta is enough.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-5.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" /> <img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-350\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-4.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Wedding Ceremony &amp; Reception</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>The wedding and reception ceremony is a great time for you to try out various designer wears and the latest trends, however, we presage you to not go over the top in excitement.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, rule out blatantly simple attires like salwars or kurtas. Since the wedding is a traditional event, it is best for you to be garbed in traditional clothing. Gowns, trousers, crop-top, skirts or anything too close-fitting or skimpy is a huge NO.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-352\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-6.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"1332\" height=\"1999\" />\r\n\r\nYour best option is to go with a Saree or the second best attire- Lehenga. If you’re a guest at the wedding, don’t wear anything too bright or a saree or lehenga that is covered with embroideries or embellishments. Wedding Reception', 'What to wear to a Bangladeshi wedding as a female guest', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '343-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-30 11:44:59', '2018-09-30 11:44:59', '', 343, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/09/30/343-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
