ht=\"1365\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-346 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/vgsgfvg.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"468\" height=\"312\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy:Reminiscence Photography</p>\r\nSince the event consists of you applying turmeric paste on the bride and groom, try to avoid long or over hanging dresses. The more you wear, the harder it will be for you to handle the excessive clothing materials in the midst of the crowd, and more the chances of you staining your precious clothes. A simple kamiz or kurta is enough.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-5.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Photoholic</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>Wedding Ceremony &amp; Reception</strong></h3>\r\n<strong> </strong>The wedding and reception ceremony is a great time for you to try out various designer wears and the latest trends, however, we presage you to not go over the top in excitement.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, rule out blatantly simple attires like salwars or kurtas. Since the wedding is a traditional event, it is best for you to be garbed in traditional clothing. Gowns, trousers, crop-top, skirts or anything too close-fitting or skimpy is a huge NO.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-352 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-to-wear-to-a-Bangladeshi-wedding-as-a-female-guest-6.jpg\" alt=\"Wedding Guest Outfits\" width=\"1332\" height=\"1999\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments/Tanvir Ali Photography</p>\r\nYour best option is to go with a Saree or the second best attire- Lehenga. If you’re a guest at the wedding, don’t wear anything too bright or a saree or lehenga that is covered with embroideries or embellishments. Wedding Reception', 'What to wear to a Bangladeshi wedding as a female guest', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '343-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-30 11:53:40', '2018-09-30 11:53:40', '', 343, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/09/30/343-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
