nd cutlery sets are the essential items she can’t do without. Gifting these might be a nice way to set her up for their future kitchen.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-387 size-full\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Gifts-for-Bride-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"327\" /><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-386\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Gifts-for-Bride-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"396\" /> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-385 aligncenter\" src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Gifts-for-Bride-8.jpg\" alt=\"Gifts for Bride\" width=\"450\" height=\"288\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFeature Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/photos/zfZmSzr7jHI?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">rawpixel</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/search/photos/gift?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a>', 'Wedding Gift for Bride', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '377-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-10-06 18:13:26', '2018-10-06 18:13:26', '', 377, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/10/06/377-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(326, 1, '2018-10-09 07:52:33', '2018-10-09 07:52:33', '<h3>\n					This is the heading\n				</h3>\n				<p>Click edit button to change this text. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Ut elit tellus, luctus nec ullamcorper mattis, pulvinar dapibus leo.</p>\n		<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">If this is your first time visiting Bangladesh since many years, or this is your first time ever here and coincidentally you\'ve been invited to your first Bangladeshi wedding during your stay, you may be inquisitive about what’s going to go down. Here we will look at some basic situations “newbies” face at our highly inimitable-traditional wedding.</h5>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1277\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</p>\n<h3><strong>What to wear</strong></h3>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image005.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</p>\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">The brighter the better. If you’re a woman, don\'t be petrified to take up a bold color attire. This will help you blend in with the guests who\'ll be dressed in vivacious colors and stunning jewelry- A saree or Lehenga is the trend. For men, you can never go wrong with a suit or a dark color Punjabi with a coati.</h5>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/26221012_819266841578274_7157282757849986845_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments</p>\n<h3><strong>Length of Wedding</strong></h3>\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">A traditional bengali wedding celebrations last an average of 7 days.  Usually, the celebration begins after the more official “Aakhd” ceremony. With Haldi nights arranged by both the brides and grooms, followed by the wedding day and then the reception.</h5>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image025.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1428\" height=\"952\" />\n<h5 style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</h5>\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">However, couples nowadays take the ceremony a step further by arranging bridal showers, Sangeet etc.</h5>\n&nbsp;\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>What can you expect to see at the wedding day?</strong></h3>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image017.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"955\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Metro Weddings</p>\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">One of the first things that might surprise Western/Non-Bangladeshi-resident guests is the bride’s and groom’s procession. For this, the groom and bride arrives to the ceremony on a flower decorated car. The bride is usually the first one to make the entrance. Guests dance around them to the beat of a dhol, a traditional drum. After that, the bride and groom meet along with their family.</h5>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image031.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"953\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Reminiscence Photography</p>\n<h3><strong>What will the Haldi/Holud ceremony be like?</strong></h3>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/31958060_1797761493623465_1599431853796753408_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Moments</p>\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">It\'s a fun party! The relatives of both the bride and groom take to the stages for a dance face off with the in laws’ family with choreographed dances. This makes the occasion more fun as it brings the families and cousins together and give the little ones something to look forward to. Because Hey! Who doesn’t like to dance silly in front of hundreds of guest along with your friends and cousins. The day ends with either some sweet EDM played by a DJ or some pop songs played by a local band.</h5>\n&nbsp;\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/wm-01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"405\" height=\"606\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo Courtesy: Wedding Mate</p>\n<h3><strong>FOOD!</strong></h3>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image033.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1054\" height=\"701\" />\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">For me, arguably the most important part of the wedding. Food is served in batches and the menu usually consists of Borhani, Polao, chicken/beef curry, vegetables, roasted chicken and if you’re lucky you might be served Kacchi. The heavy meal is then finished off by desserts like firni, jorda or mishtibhaat (Sweet rice).</h4>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/30821485_1033610443454696_4619924123552844831_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1795\" height=\"1197\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Photo Courtesy: Metro Weddings</p>\n<h3><strong>Should you bring a gift?</strong></h3>\n<img src=\"https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/image037.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1429\" height=\"952\" />\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\">You are not bound to. But if you do want to gift them something, avoid buying crockeries as they will get hundreds of similar crockeries on the day. Anything else will be a blessing!</h5>\n&nbsp;\nFeatured Photo Courtesy: Wedding Diary Bangladesh', 'WHAT TO EXPECT AT BENGALI WEDDING EVENTS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '276-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-10-09 08:46:33', '2018-10-09 08:46:33', '', 276, 'https://ayojok.com/ideas-and-stories/2018/07/22/276-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
